16/06/2008
BRCKO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Officials laid to rest on Saturday (June 14th) the remains of 47 victims of the Serb attack on the town of Brcko.
More than 5,000 friends and relatives paid their respects.
The bodies were among the 277 found in a mass grave in nearby Gorice.
Authorities previously identified and buried about 80 bodies.
Another 500 people from the Brcko area are still missing.
A total of 20,000 people are missing across BiH as a result of the 1992-1995 conflict.
(Dnevni Avaz - 15/06/08;
Fena, PBS, AP - 14/06/08)
